		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.77]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Taushar&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>The hammer is not too bad to get. If you are high enough you can single pull the named. If not I believe the Harmony works on these guys. Not 100% sure though. As the poster said, you can pull the named, kill it, loot it and turn it in for the hammer. You keep the hammer, I still have mine.<br /><br />As for Shadowscream armor, it is the cheapest way to skill up but requires hours of farming. First of all, you have to complete a quest in the kitty city that takes some time. It will get you no drop hammer and anvil. You need these to do the combines.<br /><br />Then you need two no drop loots off sonic wolves and owlbears in Hollowshade Moor. But only way you can get it is to start and manipulate a war there so one or the other occupy the southern islands. The drops are not good, 1 in about 5-10 kills.<br /><br />Then you have to get swirling shadows to finish it. They drop off either Shades in Twilight or Lesser Shades in Shadeweavers Thicket. <br /><br />All the items above stack. However, when you combine the two items from wolves and owlbears, the resulting item does not stack. It's really a pain since you need tons of them to skill up. <br /><br />If you are willing to do the quest, farming, it's certainly a cheap way to skill up. Good luck.<br /><br />Taushar</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=274297" target="akztarg">Taushar Tigris</a><br />Social Anomaly Guild, Druzzil Ro Server<br />Expert Artisan+ w/All Trophies<br />Jewelcraft (300)<br />Baking (300)<